The paper deals with the evaluation of the sum capacity of CDMA systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses fading and near-far effects, which are common issues in wireless communication networks, making it relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also mentions power control, which is a technique used to manage power consumption in communication systems, making it relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the sum capacity numerically, which involves mathematical modeling and simulation, making it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of CDMA systems, which is a topic related to communication and information theory, making it relevant to the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
